               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>Thirty-two letters from the Báb, all in Arabic, to the following persons:</p>
                     <p>(1) In answer to one of the believers (p. 1).</p>
                     <p>(2) Unspecified (p. 3).</p>
                     <p>(3) [In answer to a question of Sayyid Yabyà [of Dáráb], the "First Wahid" <lb/>(p. 9).</p>
                     <p>(4) Explaining a statement of Sayyid Kazim of Rasht (p. 26).</p>
                     <p>(5) To Sayyid Yahya "Wahid" (p. 35)</p>
                     <p>(6) Explanation of the , in the verse (Qur'an, xxxvi, 1) (p. 44).</p>
                     <p>(7) Continuation and conclusion of the above (p. 60).</p>
                     <p>(8) Explanation of the (=1+10+100+ 1000) (p. 63).</p>
                     <p>(9) Answer to Shaykh Naşiru'd-Din of Karbala, written in 1264/1848 (p. 65)</p>
                     <p>(10) On the alb (p. 77).</p>
                     <p>(11) Answer to the Mu'tamadu'd-Dawla [Minúchihr Khán] (p. 88).</p>
                     <p>(12) Answer to the Governor of Shúshtar (p. 93).</p>
                     <p>(13) Answer to a student on the queries in the Qur'an (p. 100).</p>
                     <p>(14) On the Ascension (Mi'ráj) in the Land of Sád (Isfahán) (p. 104).</p>
                     <p>(15) Explanation of a tradition of the Imám Ridá (p. 106).</p>
                     <p>(16) Answer to Hajji Muhammad, written from Mákú (p. 108).</p>
                     <p>(17) Answer to an enquirer in Isfahán (p. 111).</p>
                     <p>(18) Answer to Sayyid Asadu'lláh of Qazwin (p. 115), dated Jumádà 1, 1263 <lb/>April-May, 1847, from "the Prison in the Mountain" (p. 116).</p>
                     <p>(19) Answer to Mullá Rajab 'Alí [Janáb-i-Qahir] (p. 120).</p>
                     <p>(20) Answer to Sayyid Ahmad Aqá-záda (p. 126).</p>
                     <p>(21) Answer to Mírzá Muḥammad 'Alí (p. 127).</p>
                     <p>(22) Answer to Mírzá 'Abdu'l-Wahháb Munshí (p. 131).</p>
                     <p>(23) Answer to the father of Sayyid Husayn, written from Mákú (p. 133).</p>
                     <p>(24) To Janáb-i-Táhira (Qurratu'l-'Ayn), from Máká (p. 135).</p>
                     <p>(25) Answer to Mullá Aḥmad Abdál, from Mákú (p. 138).</p>
                     <p>(26) To Sayyid Abul Hasan, commentary on the Morning Prayer (p. 143)</p>
                     <p>(27) Commenting on the "Verse of Light" (t) (p. 155).</p>
                     <p>(28) Answer to Asad (p. 171).</p>
                     <p>(29) To Mirzá Najaf-quli (p. 189).</p>
                     <p>(30) To two persons from "the Land of Paradise" (a)</p>
                     <p>(p. 192).</p>
                     <p>(31) To Mulla Ahmad (p. 196).</p>
                     <p>(32) Letter to the 'Ulamá (p. 224).</p>
                  </summary>
